{
  "title": "NP Player Events",
  "cells": [
    {
      "type": "text",
      "data": "<div style=\"word-wrap: break-word; -webkit-nbsp-mode: space; -webkit-line-break: after-white-space; white-space: normal;\">\n<p style=\"color: rgb(54, 61, 76); font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 13px;\"><font face=\"Helvetica\">Order: loadstart -&gt; loadedmetadata -&gt; loadeddata -&gt; loadedalldata</font></p>\n<p style=\"color: rgb(54, 61, 76); font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 13px;\"><font face=\"Helvetica\">loadedalldata is custom to video.js, but the rest are defined by the html5 video spec if you want more specifics on them.</font></p>\n<p style=\"color: rgb(54, 61, 76); font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 13px;\"><font face=\"Helvetica\">You can play around with this jsbin to get a little better idea on events <a href=\"http://jsbin.com/hunuluno/4\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 128, 255);\">http://jsbin.com/hunuluno/4</a></font></p>\n<p style=\"color: rgb(54, 61, 76); font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 13px;\"><font face=\"Helvetica\">We use loadstart to know that the player is initialized, but more specifically if it’s re-initialized in the case of giving it a new source to play.</font></p>\n<p style=\"color: rgb(54, 61, 76); font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 13px;\"><font face=\"Helvetica\">The ready event is pretty similar but is mainly waiting for the playback element to be ready to receive commands. So more likely just before loadstart.</font></p>\n<div style=\"color: rgb(54, 61, 76); font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 13px;\"><font face=\"Helvetica\">If you want to be able to seek (currentTime), you’d need to load() or preload=“auto” the video and then wait for loadedmetadata or later, otherwise the player will error telling you it’s not ready.</font></div>\n<div style=\"color: rgb(54, 61, 76); font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 13px;\"><br/></div>\n<div style=\"color: rgb(54, 61, 76); font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 13px;\">FROM DAVID:</div>\n<div><b style=\"font-weight:normal;\"><span style=\"font-size:14.666666666666666px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;\">18 Aug: Is there any advantage using one of the script blocks over the other, as long as nothing else will be done in the “ready” part of the first example</span></b></div>\n<div><b style=\"font-weight:normal;\"><br/></b>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><b style=\"font-weight:normal;\"><span style=\"font-size:14.666666666666666px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&lt;script type=&quot;text/javascript&quot;&gt;</span></b></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><b style=\"font-weight:normal;\"><span style=\"font-size:14.666666666666666px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;\"> videojs('myPlayerID').ready(function(){</span></b></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><b style=\"font-weight:normal;\"><span style=\"font-size:14.666666666666666px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;\">   var myPlayer = this;</span></b></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><b style=\"font-weight:normal;\"><span style=\"font-size:14.666666666666666px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;\">   myPlayer.on('loadedmetadata',function(){</span></b></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><b style=\"font-weight:normal;\"><span style=\"font-size:14.666666666666666px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;\">     ...      </span></b></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><b style=\"font-weight:normal;\"><span style=\"font-size:14.666666666666666px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;\">   })</span></b></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><b style=\"font-weight:normal;\"><span style=\"font-size:14.666666666666666px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;\"> });</span></b></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><b style=\"font-weight:normal;\"><span style=\"font-size:14.666666666666666px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&lt;/script&gt;</span></b></p>\n<b style=\"font-weight:normal;\"><br/></b>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><b style=\"font-weight:normal;\"><span style=\"font-size:14.666666666666666px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&lt;script type=&quot;text/javascript&quot;&gt;</span></b></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><b style=\"font-weight:normal;\"><span style=\"font-size:14.666666666666666px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;\"> videojs('myPlayerID').on('loadedmetadata', function(){</span></b></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><b style=\"font-weight:normal;\"><span style=\"font-size:14.666666666666666px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;\">   var myPlayer = this;</span></b></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><b style=\"font-weight:normal;\"><span style=\"font-size:14.666666666666666px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;\">     ...</span></b></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><b style=\"font-weight:normal;\"><span style=\"font-size:14.666666666666666px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;\">   })</span></b></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><b style=\"font-weight:normal;\"><span style=\"font-size:14.666666666666666px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;\"> });</span></b></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><b style=\"font-weight:normal;\"><span style=\"font-size:14.666666666666666px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&lt;/script&gt;</span></b></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 38, 0);\"><b style=\"font-weight:normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The second one is better. The “ready” event only really exists so that the Flash-based player fallback can load asynchronously. In general, if you have code that works with HTML5-spec events and code that uses Brightcove Player specific events, prefer the version that uses HTML5.</span></b></span></p>\n</div>\n<div><br/></div>\n</div>"
    }
  ]
}